@NODE Main "CLOSEPORT"
@TOC "rexx.guide/APPENDIX D"
@{b}CLOSEPORT()@{ub}

Usage:@{b}CLOSEPORT(name)@{ub}

Closes the message port specified by the name argument, which must have been
allocated by a call to @{"OPENPORT()" LINK "OPENPORT/main"} within the current ARexx program. Any messages
received but not yet @{"REPLY" LINK "REPLY/main"}ed are automatically returned with the return code
set to 10.

See also: @{"OPENPORT()" LINK "OPENPORT/main"}

Example:
@{fg shine}
        call closeport myport
@{fg text}
@ENDNODE
